ygData.msgSnippet: Hola, Melefante. Think about going to Oasis too. Nice place. I spent most of my teens there. Never a shortage of people to group with and really large level
ygData.messageBody:
Hola, Melefante.

Think about going to Oasis too. Nice place. I spent most of my teens there. Never a shortage of people to group with and really large level span. Just watch out for the Spectors, SG's and Lockjaw :)

Chervis

On Sun, 22 Sep 2002 15:24:38
Meleficent Ouverts wrote:
>
>hey there, thanks sooo much for the ideas, they were wonderful
>i am in quynos b/c my bfriend plays and tp me there from fay. we play together, well we played together when i was a lower lvl but now he is busy and i am looking for a new place to call my home. i am thinking about going back to fay, but i dunno, i have a great weapon, i have some claws that are wonderful and hit for about 22 points each contact. very nice!!!!
>i joined a guild now, the knights of shadowfall on the tribunal server. i am gonna try and get around some of my fellow guildies, hahahah
>if you are ever around qeynos or surefall glade, or karana, please shoot me a tell, i would love to group with you!!!!!!!!!!!!!! :)
>Melefante-woodelf/ranger lvl 13
>
> jonathanv_00 wrote:Well, 15, almost 16 WE Ranger here, so let me tell you where I've
>been.
>
>1-9, or so - Greater Faydark/Crushbone, doing the orcs and Ranger
>Newbie armor quests. Why'd you relocate to Qeynos, anyway? Our
>(Wood Elf) armor and weapon quests are all centered in GFay. But now
>that you're 12, they may not be worth doing.
>9-11 - Ocean of Tears, kiling Alluring Sirens. Jump off the boat at
>either set of islands between Butcherblock and Freeport. You'll see
>the Sirens. Watch out for the Goblins, too.
>12-13 - Steamfont, collecting micro servers for the Trueshot quest
>later on
>14-current - Nybright sisters in Lesser Faydark.
>
>After this I'm headed to the Warrens, but am going to wait for Dual
>Wield at 17. Hate to get out there, then have to go someplace else
>to train.
>
>I do have a very good weapon, which makes some of this a bit easier.
>
>Hope this helps.
>
